-- CJ Land Holdings Seeks $618 Million in Hong Kong Initial Public Offering
-- B y   F o x   H u
-- 2010-10-25T02:10:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-25/cj-land-holdings-seeks-618-million-in-hong-kong-initial-public-offering.html
CJ Land Holdings Ltd., a developer
in eastern China, plans to raise as much as HK$4.8 billion ($618
million) in an initial public offering in Hong Kong to acquire
land and repay loans, according to a term sheet sent to
investors today.  One billion shares in CJ Land are being offered at HK$3.20
to HK$4.80 each, according to the document. BOC International
Holdings Ltd., Bank of America Corp.â€™s Merrill Lynch unit,
Citigroup Inc. and Macquarie Group Ltd. are managing the sale.  Of the stock offered, 90 percent is new shares and 10
percent existing equity, the term sheet shows. The developer
plans to set the price for the shares on Nov. 4 and start
trading on Nov. 11.  Pricing at the high end of the range would give CJ Land a
market capitalization of HK$19.2 billion, according to the term
sheet.  Cornerstone investors in the IPO include Chosen Elite Ltd.,
a unit of Cheung Kong (Holdings) Ltd., and Chow Tai Fook Nominee
Ltd., a company owned by billionaire  Cheng Yu-tung , the term
sheet shows.  Some 81 percent of the proceeds will be used to acquire
land, while another 14 percent will be used to repay bank loans,
according to the terms.  To contact the reporter on this story:
